.\" Manpage for vsmtp
.\" Please open a github issue to correct errors or typos.
.TH man 1 "05 May 2022" "1.0.0" "vsmtp man page"
.SH NAME
vsmtp \- High performance MTA 
.SH SYNOPSIS
vsmtp [OPTIONS] <SUBCOMMANDS>
.SH DESCRIPTION
vSMTP is a next-gen MTA written in RUST.
.SH OPTIONS
.br
-c, --config <CONFIG> Path of the vSMTP configuration file (toml format)
.br
-h, --help Print help information
.br
-V, --version Print version information
.br
-n, --no-daemon Do not run the program as a daemon
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.br
config-diff Show the difference between the loaded config and the default one
.br
config-show Show the loaded config (as serialized json format)
.br
help Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH SEE ALSO
vsmtp(1) 
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Team viridIKT (https://viridit.com/)
